               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390408-name-1512" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1512" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1512" type="surname" value="WESTMORLAND"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390408-name-1512" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES WESTMORLAND</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable F</hi> 147.) On the 1st of April I was at Greenwich fair—I saw the prisoner put his hand into a gentleman's pocket, take out a white pocket handkerchief, and put it into his own right-hand trowsers' pocket—I took him into custody, and went to inform the gentleman, but the crowd made a rush, which sent me two or three yards away, and I lost the gentleman—I do not know him—I found the hand-kerchief in the prisoner's pocket—it is marked "W. B."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I picked the handkerchief up, when he caught hold of my collar, and said, "You are the <hi rend="italic">chap</hi> I have been looking for." <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I saw him put his hand into the gentleman's pocket, and take it out—it was quite clean—I found the blade of a knife in his pocket.</p>
